# QuantumShield – Post-Quantum Cryptography Demo (Java)

QuantumShield is an educational Java-based platform that demonstrates the transition from classical cryptography to post-quantum cryptography.

It combines:
- Quantum Key Distribution (BB84 simulation)
- Post-Quantum Cryptography (Toy Lattice KEM)
- AES-GCM encrypted chat system
- RSA vulnerability demonstration
- Performance benchmarking

📄 Full project report: :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}


## 🚀 Features

- **BB84 Simulation**
  - Simulates quantum key distribution
  - Detects eavesdropping via error rate
  - Generates secure session keys

- **Lattice-based KEM (Toy Implementation)**
  - Demonstrates post-quantum key exchange
  - Encapsulation & decapsulation workflow

- **Secure Chat System**
  - AES-128 GCM encryption
  - Multi-client server support
  - Real-time encrypted messaging

- **RSA Attack Demo**
  - Brute-force factorization of small RSA keys
  - Demonstrates classical cryptography weakness

- **Benchmarking**
  - Compares RSA vs Lattice KEM performance



## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- Java (JDK 8+)
- Java Cryptography Architecture (JCA)
- TCP Sockets
- Multithreading (ExecutorService)



